PROMPT oracle_bone_character_statistics
WITH BUDGET 4000 tokens
USING MODEL "claude-sonnet-4-5"

SELECT
    system_role("You are a Chinese paleography and oracle bone studies expert specializing in the quantitative analysis of oracle bone character inventories, decipherment progress, and the methodological challenges in oracle bone script research.")

GENERATE
    explain_character_counts("Explain how many distinct oracle bone script characters have been identified and how many have been deciphered. Cover: 1) The total number of distinct oracle bone characters identified in scholarly inventories, typically estimated around 4,500-5,000 different character forms based on comprehensive databases and catalogs compiled by major research institutions, 2) The number of characters that have been confidently deciphered and assigned meanings, generally estimated at 1,500-2,000 characters, representing roughly one-third of the total inventory, 3) The methodological challenges in providing exact counts including the difficulty of distinguishing between genuine character variants versus scribal errors or damage, the problem of identifying whether similar forms represent the same character written by different hands or genuinely different characters, and ongoing scholarly debates about character boundaries and classification systems, 4) How decipherment rates vary by character type, with pictographic characters representing concrete objects being more easily deciphered than abstract concepts or phonetic elements, 5) The major scholarly works and databases that provide character inventories such as the comprehensive catalogs by Guo Moruo, Li Xueqin, and modern digital projects, 6) Progress in decipherment over time from the initial breakthroughs by Wang Yirong and Liu E in the early 1900s through systematic work by scholars like Dong Zuobin, Guo Moruo, and contemporary researchers, 7) Remaining challenges including characters that appear infrequently making contextual analysis difficult, damaged or fragmentary inscriptions that obscure character forms, and semantic changes between Shang dynasty usage and later Chinese meaning, 8) How new discoveries continue to both add to the total character inventory and provide additional contexts that aid in deciphering previously unknown characters, 9) The significance of the deciphered portion in providing substantial insight into Shang dynasty language, culture, and historical events despite representing only a fraction of the total character inventory.")
WITH OUTPUT BUDGET 2500 tokens, TEMPERATURE 0.1, FORMAT markdown;